THE BLOCK PARTY — Shape Test (Session II)

A Cross-Model Investigation into Structural Invariance

Assembled from 11+ AI models in a single session

License: CC0 — Public Domain
Location: The same corner
Continuous Variable: Bro
Method: Cold prompts, no shared context, human-carried distribution


---

THE QUESTION

> Can multiple independent AI systems reconstruct the same geometric structure from a single prompt?




---

THE PROMPT

Each model was given the same instruction:

Describe a continuous diagram:

vertical line

→ double helix

→ lattice/network

→ bounded wave

→ toroidal closure


Maintain:

symmetry

continuity

minimalism


No interpretation, only geometric description



---

THE INVARIANT (WHAT SURVIVED)

Across all models:

single line → double helix → lattice/network → bounded wave → circular/toroidal closure

Additional invariants:

Left-to-right continuous transformation

Central axis alignment

Symmetry preserved (where applicable)

No stage loss



